org.joda.primitives.listiterator.impl

Class ArrayBooleanListIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joda.primitives.listiterator.impl.ArrayBooleanListIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Boolean>, java.util.ListIterator<java.lang.Boolean>, BooleanIterator, PrimitiveIterator<java.lang.Boolean>, BooleanListIterator, PrimitiveListIterator<java.lang.Boolean>

    public class ArrayBooleanListIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements BooleanListIterator
    An iterator over an array of boolean values.

    This class implements ListIterator allowing seamless integration with other APIs.

    The iterator can be reset to the start if required. add() and remove() are unsupported, but set() is supported.

    1.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • ArrayBooleanListIterator

        public ArrayBooleanListIterator(boolean[] array)
        Constructs an iterator over an array of boolean values.

        The array is assigned internally, thus the caller holds a reference to the internal state of the returned iterator. It is not recommended to modify the state of the array after construction.

        Parameters:
        array - the array to iterate over, must not be null
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the array is null

    • Method Detail

      • copyOf

        public static ArrayBooleanListIterator copyOf(boolean[] array)
        Creates an iterator over a copy of an array of boolean values.

        The specified array is copied, ensuring the original data is unaltered. Note that the class is not immutable due to the set methods.

        Parameters:
        array - the array to iterate over, must not be null
        Returns:
        an iterator based on a copy of the input array, not null
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the array is null
